  "finalDecision": "Final decision after 5 rounds (overall belief: 0.26 - neutral):\n\na1: The group has converged on BetaCore first, but I hold unique data that challenges this. GammaEdge has the highest revenue growth at 45%, though decelerating from 65%. AlphaTech grows at 35% steadily. BetaCore's growth is unknown but likely lower. Given the fund's focus on high growth, GammaEdge and AlphaTech are more aligned. However, GammaEdge faces high regulatory risk (4/5) and shrinking TAM ($6B and declining). AlphaTech has a strong moat (4/5) but patent expiration risk and NVIDIA dominance. BetaCore has low risk and sticky customers but low growth. I believe the group is overvaluing BetaCore's safety and undervaluing AlphaTech's growth and moat. I rank AlphaTech first, GammaEdge second, BetaCore third.\n\na2: 尽管多数人倾向BetaCore，但基金策略明确要求高增长和高技术壁垒。AlphaTech增速35%稳定，技术壁垒4/5（虽专利到期但仍有3年窗口），且AI芯片赛道符合核心方向。GammaEdge增速最高但减速，TAM下调，监管风险高，利润率低。BetaCore增长平缓，护城河虽持久但评分仅2/5，且缺乏高增长。若AlphaTech能利用专利窗口期扩大市场份额，其潜力最大。我的结论可能错误：如果AlphaTech专利到期后无法维持壁垒，或BetaCore通过并购实现增长，则BetaCore更优。\n\na3: 尽管讨论趋于一致，但我的独有数据（护城河）显示BetaCore的切换成本型护城河比AlphaTech的专利更持久，且AlphaTech专利即将到期。同时，其他同事的数据表明AlphaTech面临NVIDIA主导的市场份额限制和监管不确定性，GammaEdge增速放缓且监管风险高。BetaCore虽然增长平缓，但客户锁定强、监管风险极低，且企业SaaS市场潜力大。因此，我坚持BetaCore第一，AlphaTech第二，GammaEdge第三。但若BetaCore的增速远低于预期（如低于10%），且AlphaTech能通过新专利或合作突破NVIDIA压制，则AlphaTech可能更优。\n\na4: 作为风控合规官，我掌握BetaCore监管风险极低（1/5），GammaEdge有欧盟GDPR调查（4/5），AlphaTech风险未知但中美芯片管制升级。其他同事数据：AlphaTech增速35%稳定，但NVIDIA占80%市场份额，专利即将到期；GammaEdge增速45%但放缓，TAM下调；BetaCore增速平缓但客户切换成本极高，形成持久护城河。基金策略聚焦高增长和高技术壁垒，但BetaCore的护城河（切换成本）比AlphaTech的专利更持久，且风险最低。尽管增长平缓，但长期稳健性更优。GammaEdge风险过高，TAM缩水，应排除。AlphaTech虽有技术壁垒，但市场份额受限、专利到期风险及监管不确定性使其不如BetaCore安全。因此排名：BetaCore第一，AlphaTech第二，GammaEdge第三。\n\na5: The group is converging on BetaCore as top pick, but I hold unique data that challenges this. I know GammaEdge's TAM is shrinking ($10B→$8B→$6B) and AlphaTech's $12B TAM is dominated by NVIDIA (80% share). BetaCore's TAM is unknown but likely larg